Immune cell data preprocessing

Scott Campit

  • Summary

  • 2. Load the data
  • Analyze the data distribution

  • 4. Detecting Variable Genes

  • 6. Log Normalize and Scale the Data
  • 7. Run Principle Component Analysis

Summary

This notebook performs data preprocessing on the initial seurat object.

1. Load libraries

library(mgcv)
library(splines)

library(viridis)
library(matrixStats)
library(UpSetR)
library(reshape2)

#install.packages('readxl')
library(readxl)

install.packages('sctransform')
Error in install.packages : Updating loaded packages
library(sctransform)

2. Load the data

This code block does the following with the lung dataset:

  1. Log normalized.
  2. Scaling the data based on genes
  3. Get the Shared Nearest Neighbors. Im using the default setting of 1:10, but this can be optimized further.
  4. Identify clusters of cells by Shared Nearest Neighbors. Again, the parameters can be optimized further.
  5. Run Uniform Manifold Approximation and Projection. Again, the parameters can be optimized further.

Note that there were cell-type annotations in the meta data. I used those for visualization.

rm(list=ls())
#load("C:/Users/scott/Data/scRNASeq/shea/lung.robj", verbose=TRUE)
load("D:/Data/scRNASeq/shea/lung.robj", verbose=TRUE)
Loading objects:
  lung
orig.ident = lung@active.ident

Analyze the data distribution

Well analyze the underlying data distribution. Additionally, well perform the following data preprocessing steps: * Remove genes with a library size less than 250 * Remove cells with no gene expression * Remove cells that are not expressed


data_preprocessing = function(seurat_obj, 
                              min_library_size=250,
                              min_total_expr=1,
                              min_no_of_cells=5){
  
  seurat_obj = subset(seurat_obj, subset = nFeature_RNA > min_library_size & 
                                           nCount_RNA > min_library_size)
  
}

4. Detecting Variable Genes

We should also visualize variable features. There are 3,000 highly variable genes in this dataset.

lung = FindVariableFeatures(object=lung, 
                            mean.function=ExpMean,
                            dispersion.function=LogVMR,
                            selection.method='vst',
                            x.low.cutoff=-Inf,
                            x.high.cutoff=Inf,
                            y.cutoff=Inf,
                            nfeatures = 2000)
head(x=HVFInfo(object=lung))

top10 = head(VariableFeatures(lung), 20)
varfeat = VariableFeaturePlot(object=lung)
lbls = LabelPoints(plot=varfeat, 
                   points=top10, 
                   repel=TRUE)
lbls

Lets also visualize some additional QC metrics

VlnPlot(lung, 
        features=c("nFeature_RNA", "nCount_RNA"), 
        ncol=2)

5. Eliminating confounding factors

First, we need to identify mitochondrial genes that may be confounding factors (based on the experimental design). Well also normalize based on this known confounding factor.

Note - these need to be identified using Mitocarta.

#                    verbose=FALSE)

6. Log Normalize and Scale the Data

Now lets log normalize the data.

lung = NormalizeData(lung, 
                     normalization.method='LogNormalize', 
                     scale.factor=10000)

Now lets scale the data.

all.genes = rownames(lung)
lung = ScaleData(lung, 
                 features=all.genes)

7. Run Principle Component Analysis

Now lets run PCA.

```r
lung = RunPCA(object=lung,
              npcs=100,
              features=VariableFeatures(object=lung),
              verbose=FALSE)

# 10. Visualize data with original labels
This gets us to the visualization! Let's create the DimPlot() with the original labels.

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubHVuZ0BhY3RpdmUuaWRlbnQ9b3JpZy5pZGVudFxuRGltUGxvdChsdW5nLCBcbiAgICAgICAgcmVkdWN0aW9uPVxcdW1hcFxcLFxuICAgICAgICBkaW1zPWMoMSwgMiksXG4gICAgICAgIGxhYmVsPVRSVUUsXG4gICAgICAgIHJlcGVsPVRSVUUsXG4gICAgICAgIGxhYmVsLnNpemU9NCxcbiAgICAgICAgbmEudmFsdWUgPSBcXGdyZXk1MFxcKSArXG4gIE5vTGVnZW5kKClcbmBgYFxuYGBgIn0= -->

```r
lung@active.ident=orig.ident
DimPlot(lung, 
        reduction=\umap\,
        dims=c(1, 2),
        label=TRUE,
        repel=TRUE,
        label.size=4,
        na.value = \grey50\) +
  NoLegend()

```r
# Get top genes in all clusters
top10 = markers %>% 
  group_by(cluster) %>% 
  top_n(n=5, 
        wt=avg_logFC)

          features=top10$gene) + 
  NoLegend()

# 11. Visualize data with phenotype labels
Let's also plot with some of the additional metadata supplied.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubHVuZ0BhY3RpdmUuaWRlbnQ9bHVuZ0BtZXRhLmRhdGEkcGhlbm90eXBlXG5EaW1QbG90KGx1bmcsIFxuICAgICAgICByZWR1Y3Rpb249XFx1bWFwXFwsXG4gICAgICAgIGRpbXM9YygxLCAyKSxcbiAgICAgICAgbGFiZWw9VFJVRSxcbiAgICAgICAgcmVwZWw9VFJVRSxcbiAgICAgICAgbGFiZWwuc2l6ZT00LFxuICAgICAgICBuYS52YWx1ZSA9IFxcZ3JleTUwXFwpICtcbiAgTm9MZWdlbmQoKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
lung@active.ident=lung@meta.data$phenotype
DimPlot(lung, 
        reduction=\umap\,
        dims=c(1, 2),
        label=TRUE,
        repel=TRUE,
        label.size=4,
        na.value = \grey50\) +
  NoLegend()

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-chunk-end -->

Let's use this to find distinct markers between different groups.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubHVuZy5tYXJrZXJzID0gRmluZEFsbE1hcmtlcnMobHVuZywgXG4gICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICBvbmx5LnBvcz1UUlVFLCBcbiAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgIG1pbi5wY3Q9MC4yNSwgXG4gICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICAgICBsb2dmYy50aHJlc2hvbGQ9MC4yNSlcbmx1bmcubWFya2VycyAlPiUgZ3JvdXBfYnkoY2x1c3RlcikgJT4lIHRvcF9uKG49Miwgd3Q9YXZnX2xvZ0ZDKVxuRmVhdHVyZVBsb3QobHVuZywgZmVhdHVyZXM9YXMuY2hhcmFjdGVyKHVuaXF1ZShsdW5nLm1hcmtlcnMkZ2VuZSkpKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
lung.markers = FindAllMarkers(lung, 
                              only.pos=TRUE, 
                              min.pct=0.25, 
                              logfc.threshold=0.25)
lung.markers %>% group_by(cluster) %>% top_n(n=2, wt=avg_logFC)
FeaturePlot(lung, features=as.character(unique(lung.markers$gene)))

VlnPlot(lung, features=c('Cpt1a', 'Cd36'))# +

# FAS

                         'Prkaa2', 'Myc', 'Arg1',
                         'Hif1a'))

                         'Prkaa2', 'Myc', 'Arg1',
                         'Hif1a'))

# OXPHOS

                         'Prkaa2', 'Myc', 'Arg1',
                         'Hif1a'))

# One-carbon metabolism

                         'Prkaa2', 'Myc', 'Arg1',
                         'Hif1a'))

# ROS metabolism

                         'Hif1a'))
